      "span_text": "Different with Pyrococcus species, Pa. pacificus does not contain \"saccharolytic gene island\" and \"maltose and trehalose degradation gene\" (5), which carries a set of genes responsible for the utilization of cellulose, laminarin, agar, maltose, trehalose, and other ␤-linked polysaccharides. These genes are also absent in Thermococcus species except Thermococcus sibiricus [CITATION_1] ."
